productName: Mousse
bullet1: A Pirelli Mousse is a technologically advanced product characterized by the presence of self-pressurizing agents capable of creating a very large number of gas bubbles inside the mousse making the product immune to punctures
bullet2: When new they are equivalent to an inner tube inflated to 0.9 bar (equivalent to approximately 13 PSI); this pressure declines gradually along the life of the mousse which must be replaced when it becomes too soft
bullet3: Immune to punctures and abrasions; developed by Pirelli for riders who compete in every kind of competition whether it be a race in the desert or a Cross championship trial
bullet4: Technically the Mousse is a butyl ring with a honeycomb structure the cells of which are filled with gas so as to simulate the effect of an inner tube
bullet5: The Mousse is surrounded by a thin external membrane designed to make it easy to fit on different sized tires
bullet6: Toroidal-shaped expanded-foam inserts replace the traditional inner tube on off-road motorcycles
bullet7: 12-pack of 60-gram mounting lube tubes also available separately
bullet8: Designed for use with Pirelli tires on off-road surfaces
bullet9: Sold each with mounting gel lube
